# Force LF in the working tree on every platform. The toolchain expects LF
# everywhere — rustfmt (`newline_style = "Unix"`), biome / taplo / yamlfmt, and
# `.editorconfig` all assume it. Without this, Git's `core.autocrlf=true` (the
# Windows default) checks files out as CRLF, so `just fmt` / `just lint` and the
# lefthook pre-commit hooks fail on a native Windows host even though the repo
# blobs are LF. `text=auto` still lets Git auto-detect and leave binaries alone.
#
# Existing Windows clones: after pulling this file, run once to refresh the
# working tree to LF:  git add --renormalize . && git checkout .
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binaries — never normalize these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.webp binary
*.rgba binary
*.pam binary
*.ico binary
*.exe binary
*.svg text eol=lf
